quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  29,7,"Those who believe and do righteous deeds, from them We will remove all sin that may be in them, and We will reward them according to the best of their deeds"
  29,8,"We have enjoined on humanity kindness to parents, but if either of them tries to force you to join in worship anything with Me of which you do not know, do not follow them. You all have to return to me, and I will tell you the truth of all that you did"
  29,9,"And those who believe and work righteous deeds, We will admit them to the company of the righteous"
  29,10,"Then there are some people who say, “We believe in God.” But when they suffer affliction in the cause of God, they perceive the human inflicted problem as if it were the punishment of God, and if help comes to you from your Lord, they are sure to say, “We were with you.” Does God not know best all that is in the heart of all creation"
  29,11,"And God most certainly knows those who believe, and just as certainly, those who are hypocrites"
  29,12,"And the unbelievers say to those who believe, “Follow our way, and we will bear the consequences of your faults.” Never in the least will they bear their consequences, in fact they are liars"
  29,13,"They will however, bear their own burdens, and share the burdens of others, and on the Day of Accountability they will be called to account for their lies"
  29,14,"Indeed We sent Noah to his people, and he stayed among them a thousand years less fifty, but the flood overwhelmed them while they persisted in harmful deeds"